Description: Fragment of lower neck of Egyptian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium, grey-brown; much straw temper. Nile clay? Rectangular stamp with floral motif symbol.
Curator's comments: Clay points strongly to the provenance of Naukratis. The piece could be from a tile or a large amphora. In addition Boston, MFA, Res.87.299 is an almost identical piece, proving the provenance of both fragments.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1311)
